      <body>Is that really true? both 1.2 and 2.0 eventually use each_with_index to set the value of the counter when rendering each item in the collection. add_counter_to_local_assigns is only called when rendering a single item (it is a bit weird that the default value of that counter is 1)

I believe Pratik was talking about making it start from 1 in a future version</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Is that really true? both 1.2 and 2.0 eventually use
each_with_index to set the value of the counter when rendering each
item in the collection. add_counter_to_local_assigns is only called
when rendering a single item (it is a bit weird that the default
value of that counter is 1)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I believe Pratik was talking about making it start from 1 in a
future version&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
